Download and install on Mac

1. Download and install "Darwinports".
	Go to http://darwinports.com/

2. Download and install "pdftohtml".
	Open a terminal and type in this follow command line : 
		'sudo port install pdftohtml'
	Enter root password and hit return.

3. Use "pdftohtml".
	You can use this follow command line :
		'pdftohtml -c <PDF-file>'
	If you don't want to type all command line each time 
	you can use this script (launchConversion.sh) with this parameter :
		'<PDF-file>'
	
4. Options.
	Usage: pdftohtml [options] <PDF-file> [<html-file> <xml-file>]
		-f <int>          : first page to convert
  		-l <int>          : last page to convert
  		-q                : don't print any messages or errors
  		-h                : print usage information
  		-help             : print usage information
  		-p                : exchange .pdf links by .html
  		-c                : generate complex document
  		-i                : ignore images
  		-noframes         : generate no frames
  		-stdout           : use standard output
  		-zoom <fp>        : zoom the pdf document (default 1.5)
  		-xml              : output for XML post-processing
  		-hidden           : output hidden text
  		-enc <string>     : output text encoding name
  		-dev <string>     : output device name for Ghostscript (png16m, jpeg etc)
  		-v                : print copyright and version info
  		-opw <string>     : owner password (for encrypted files)
  		-upw <string>     : user password (for encrypted files)
	
Links :
http://darwinports.com/
http://sourceforge.net/projects/pdftohtml/